{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d60cffaa-90d7-4bf0-b765-0e109821fa4a","content":"No files exist in the working directory — there's no existing project to edit. I'll explain how to convert your page and catch errors at build time.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add the `x:DataType` attribute** to your `ContentPage` (or any element where you set `BindingContext`):\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <StackLayout Padding=\"20\">\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Slider Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat's the only XAML change needed. The `xmlns:vm` import + `x:DataType` directive tells the compiler the type of `BindingContext`, so every `{Binding ...}` is verified against `SettingsViewModel` at compile time.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**2. Enable `$(MauiStrictXamlCompilation)`** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith this flag, any `{Binding}` that references a property not found on the declared `x:DataType` becomes a **build error** (not just a runtime silent failure).\n\n## Key Points\n\n- **Scope**: `x:DataType` applies to the element and all its descendants. You can override it on a child element if a sub-tree binds to a different type.\n- **Opting out**: Use `x:DataType=\"\"` (empty string) on a specific element to disable compiled bindings locally (e.g., for `DataTrigger` bindings to self).\n- **Performance**: Compiled bindings skip runtime reflection, so they're faster than classic bindings.\n- **Typo = build error**: Misspelling `Theme` as `Themee` will now fail the build immediately, instead of silently showing nothing at runtime.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"96e69148-082c-4ee0-bbcc-5c939ee0446d","outputTokens":578,"requestId":"B7D0:2A1B2F:1283D5:181548:69FFD730"},"id":"f2ba84e8-6c10-4b51-b62f-6bafaf7dd915","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:20.930Z","parentId":"748c3acf-ce4e-4db6-8439-b7d962edf1b8"}
